content: Testing methodology creates a lot of misinformation and does not align with Monash and many of the serving sizes are ridiculously small. Uninstalling.

Great app! Very helpful and accurate. Would be nice to have an option to filter by Country as not every brand is available worldwide.
So far so good

App works again without crashing. Very useful app with a lot of food items that serves as an easy and quickly look up tool. UI leaves something to be desired in my opinion as the assets look like they are pictures that were enlarged a bit to much in same cases and non of it looks very native to Android. Besides that though not much to complain about. Visuals: 3 stars, functioning: 5 stars. Has had stability issues in the past.
The app is really not up to date compared to the Monash App. The serving sizes aren't always correct.

Could not find a way to contact developers. There are several incorrect 
photos. Couscous is shown instead of soy flour, red currant instead of 
cranberries, snap peas instead of frozen peas, shelling peas instead of 
snow peas, raisins instead of dates, firm banana instead of ripe banana. 
Also, What in the world is maize derived from wheat? Maize is corn, not 
wheat. The content is not super complete, but it's slowly getting better. 
This app is the face of an independent FODMAP testing lab. You're getting 
some of the most up to date FODMAP content information anywhere! I really 
appreciate being given the actual percentages of different FODMAPs. I wish 
all the foods had this info.
Useful, but 1.4gb - how is it so huge??
This app stinks, I would like a refund! Not helpful at all.
Terrible I want a refund. App doesn't have ingredients or basic items like bell peppers and oranges. Fodmap helper is much better.

Great app, really good to see percentages, I think they will be very helpful in assessing overall intakes for each meal. However it would be nice to see the percentages for all of the foods in the app, including the branded foods.
Bloody awful, a total waste, no help whatsoever. Don't bother.

Galaxy S5, app crashed the first two runs. Worked on the third run but when I search for a food, it doesn't do anything. I type a term, I hit enter, nothing happens. Two stars because I'm desperate for anyone to do anything they can about FODMAPs.
